1
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:46,087
<i>I need to talk to Papa.</i>

2
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:47,839
I know the agency doesn't allow it,

3
00:00:47,922 --> 00:00:49,799
I know it's dangerous,

4
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,718
and I know they have a point,

5
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,804
<i>and if it's true that La Morte Bianca</i>
<i>is here,</i>

6
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:57,057
I really need to talk to Papa.

7
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:20,789
Really? Where?

8
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:21,873
Somewhere here.

9
00:01:21,956 --> 00:01:23,333
- Oh, here.
- Yes.

10
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:30,256
Wait, where's Mikoy and Chiara?

11
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,925
Where's my car?

12
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,929
I'll do my own thing, and you'll do yours.

13
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:38,932
Hurry! Sianong!

14
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:58,576
And then you tell me
our protected witnesses are missing?

15
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:03,623
<i>Do you know why our agency is so small?</i>

16
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:06,918
Because we don't recruit just anyone!

17
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:11,172
<i>We carefully handpick our people.</i>
<i>If you're chosen, that means</i>

18
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,633
you're one of the best.

19
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:16,719
And then you tell me…

20
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:19,722
<i>What happened?</i>

21
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:29,274
Mikoy and Chiara escaped.

22
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:32,986
Did the Moravianos get them?

23
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:34,362
Was there an extraction?

24
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:36,447
<i>What?</i>

25
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:39,117
<i>You have so many agents there!</i>

26
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:41,661
<i>We have so many protocols.</i>

27
00:02:41,744 --> 00:02:43,746
We have so many rules!

28
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:47,500
And then you tell me, "I don't know."

29
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:54,591
Find them.

30
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,136
Before the Moravianos do.

31
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:01,848
<i>Before La Morte Bianca finds them!</i>

32
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:04,684
Before we're the last to know

33
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:07,729
where our witnesses are.

34
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:34,130
The last thing I remember,
Chiara gave me a massage.

35
00:03:34,213 --> 00:03:35,715
Me too.

36
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:37,258
Me too.

37
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:39,552
But didn't Mikoy say anything?

38
00:03:40,136 --> 00:03:42,931
Well, all throughout the night,
Mikoy barely said a word.

39
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:51,272
And what are you doing here?

40
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:53,107
Seriously?

41
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:55,068
Is this how you treat a guest?

42
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:01,115
I just wanted to visit.

43
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,584
I missed you all!

44
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,004
Are you sleeping?

45
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:21,469
You all look exhausted.

46
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,557
Agent Dara?

47
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:29,560
Why are you here?

48
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:34,107
Something's missing.

49
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:35,733
Where are the lovebirds?

50
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:38,736
How would I know?

51
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:40,738
Maybe they're in their room.

52
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:46,202
Last thing I want

53
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:49,914
is to open the door
and see something X-rated.

54
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:50,915
Ben!

55
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,084
Sorry, I'm just too handsome.

56
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:54,961
I'm not perfect.

57
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:58,006
How was I supposed to know that when they
were handing out looks and talent,

58
00:04:58,089 --> 00:05:00,300
I caught the good looks.

59
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:01,259
Ben!

60
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:09,309
That's it! You keep going on
about how handsome you are.

61
00:05:11,644 --> 00:05:13,271
I got fired, remember?

62
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:19,610
Besides, I'm not here
on official business.

63
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,071
Dara.

64
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:25,450
I saw your car on my way here.

65
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:51,517
There.

66
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,148
That's my car. No wonder it was missing.

67
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:07,742
Wait, what's with the rice cakes?

68
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:09,619
Rice cakes?

69
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:13,164
I remember Mikoy telling me about that.

70
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:16,334
Every time he goes home,
he buys fresh rice cakes

71
00:06:16,417 --> 00:06:17,960
because they're Tess's favorite.

72
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:54,956
We don't think they escaped.

73
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,166
And we don't think it was an extraction.

74
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:06,300
<i>No intentional concealment</i>

75
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:08,302
and no signs of an extraction.

76
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,680
And sir, if this was an extraction,

77
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:14,142
they wouldn't stop the car
just to buy souvenirs.

78
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:17,895
And if we're right, Mikoy just went home.

79
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,704
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

80
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:39,500
Mom! Dad!

81
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:43,921
What is it?

82
00:07:44,922 --> 00:07:47,091
Someone keeps whistling.

83
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:49,719
Mom! Dad!

84
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,096
There it is!

85
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,599
See? Someone keeps whistling. I told you.

86
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:56,517
I don't hear anything.

87
00:07:57,685 --> 00:07:58,853
Mom!

88
00:07:58,936 --> 00:07:59,854
Dad!

89
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,355
There it is again!

90
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:03,524
- Mario!
- Mom!

91
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:04,901
Dad!

92
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:06,527
There it is again!

93
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:08,154
I've been telling you all along, Tess.

94
00:08:08,237 --> 00:08:10,031
- Mikoy is alive!
- Alive--

95
00:08:20,124 --> 00:08:22,293
<i>If the Moravianos are watching,</i>

96
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:25,421
I don't want them knowing
we're making a move.

97
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:29,050
If it's La Concordat or La Morte Bianca,

98
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:31,636
I don't want them getting there first.

99
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,273
Mom! Dad!

100
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:47,401
I heard that.

101
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,487
- I heard that.
- I told you!

102
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,113
Mom! Dad!

103
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:53,616
- Mikoy!
- Mikoy?

104
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,813
- We missed you.
- I missed you too.

105
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:24,772
Dad!

106
00:09:24,855 --> 00:09:26,190
Oh, right, hold on.

107
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,777
Come here first, Mom and Dad.

108
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:35,491
Mom, I almost forgot.
I brought you something.

109
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,244
Your favorite rice cakes!

110
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:42,373
Thank you, my child.
You always remember my favorite.

111
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:43,332
Of course, Mom!

112
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:49,839
By the way, Mom, where's Angelito?

113
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:54,635
Oh, he's at the fishing village
for an outreach program.

114
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,512
He's there with his friends.

115
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:58,431
That's great!

116
00:09:58,514 --> 00:09:59,807
Too bad we missed each other.

117
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,768
I'm only here for a quick visit.

118
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,438
Okay.

119
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:08,941
Throw it away.

120
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,235
- We'll just get another one.
- No.

121
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:15,197
We also have that.
Would you like to take a picture?

122
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:20,036
Ma'am! How much is this?

123
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:21,329
Just 50 pesos, sir.

124
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,956
- Fifty.
- That's nice, sir.

125
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:30,129
Hey!

126
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:33,549
That's perfect! Isn't that
Sofie's favorite color?

127
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,634
Huh?

128
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:37,887
According to your Sofie research notes.

129
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,560
Wait, are you going
to give that to Laurence,

130
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:45,978
so he can give it to Sofie?

131
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:49,982
Yes.

132
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,233
Nice!

133
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:53,110
You're such a great wingman!

134
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:55,237
Laurence!

135
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:56,280
Come on!

136
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:57,990
Wait, you might miss me.

137
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:00,743
Why?

138
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,036
He'll give you something.

139
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,415
Try giving it to Sofie.

140
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:07,875
It's her favorite color.

141
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:11,087
- Really?
- Yes, go ahead.

142
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,005
Love you! Give me a kiss!

143
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,090
- Hey!
- Don't!

144
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:15,549
- Why?
- Later.

145
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,592
When it's just the two of us.

146
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,636
- Yes, it's the two of you!
- It's not just kiss. Just kidding!

147
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:21,138
- Why don't you give that to Sofie?
- When Luisa Mae isn't around?

148
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,352
Wow, that's so thoughtful.

149
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,895
Sofie.

150
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:30,106
I actually saw this.

151
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:31,232
Go on.

152
00:11:31,816 --> 00:11:32,650
It's really pretty.

153
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:33,692
So I thought…

154
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:34,819
I would suit you--

155
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,487
I mean, it suits you.

156
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:38,447
It suits you, of course. You're beautiful!

157
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,491
See? You look like a Girl Scout.

158
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:41,409
Right?

159
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:42,952
Here, let me.

160
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:44,078
Or do you want it in the front?

161
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,579
- No.
- No?

162
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:46,789
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

163
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:47,957
Isn't this your favorite color?

164
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,083
Thank you! Thank you!

165
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,459
Of course. It's you, after all.

166
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:51,877
They look cute together.

167
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:54,964
How could anyone resist
someone like Sofie?

168
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,882
- Thank you.
- I know, right?

169
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:07,393
You're even competing
with Taylor Swift's bridges.

170
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:09,645
Not really.

171
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:20,948
Mikoy.

172
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:23,868
Are the police still looking for you?

173
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:26,662
Not anymore, Dad.

174
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:28,622
The agency has an immunity program.

175
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:31,375
We're staying in a safe house.
Chiara is there with me.

176
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,669
Thank God.

177
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:35,671
I'm glad to hear that, son.

178
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:36,589
Yes, Mom.

179
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:38,048
What about the Valtrovis?

180
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:41,093
Are they looking for you?

181
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,846
Oh, by the way,
your father-in-law stopped by.

182
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:46,223
He was worried about Chiara too.

183
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:56,817
Who was that?

184
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:04,867
That's the second time.

185
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,168
That's the third time!

186
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:16,045
If they pass by again…

187
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,339
- What?
- That's the fourth.

188
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,763
Ma'am, here's the payment.

189
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:27,848
Thank you!

190
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,024
They changed routes.

191
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:11,308
Mikoy.

192
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:13,811
Is your mission still not over?

193
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:16,438
Not yet, Dad.

194
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:21,068
Mom, Dad, please listen carefully.

195
00:14:21,151 --> 00:14:23,320
As much as possible,
please stay inside the house.

196
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:24,864
No one should go out.

197
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,991
You already know our cover
has been compromised.

198
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:29,034
So it's safer if we all stay put for now.

199
00:14:31,078 --> 00:14:33,163
You can count on us.
We'll stay put, all right?

200
00:14:33,247 --> 00:14:34,832
Wait, what about you?

201
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:37,293
Dad, I need to go back to the safe house.

202
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,794
But don't worry.

203
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:41,839
Once all of this is over,
everything will be back to normal.

204
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:42,882
I promise.

205
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:44,967
Wait.

206
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,802
Why don't you stop by the house first?

207
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,304
Have a meal before you leave.

208
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:49,930
- That's right.
- Come on, son.

209
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,057
Come on.

210
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,767
Okay, Mom, but just for a bit.

211
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:56,687
All right. Come on, let's go.

212
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:03,527
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

213
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,746
Girls!

214
00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:14,872
Oh my!

215
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:16,999
The Pinagpala family!

216
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:19,835
Their house exploded!

217
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:22,755
- It was absolutely devastating!
- It's about the Pinagpalas.

218
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:25,549
Nothing was left,
not even their little bakery!

219
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:26,508
Nothing!

220
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:27,801
Just piles of rubble!

221
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:29,345
You know what's strange?

222
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:31,180
Why was it only the Pinagpalas' house
that exploded?

223
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,598
That definitely wasn't an accident.

224
00:15:32,681 --> 00:15:33,891
It was intentional.

225
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:36,518
But the Pinagpalas don't have any enemies.

226
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,312
They're such kind people!

227
00:15:38,395 --> 00:15:40,439
You know, I noticed the other day,

228
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:41,690
the village watchmen
were patrolling nonstop.

229
00:15:41,774 --> 00:15:42,858
But they still got through!

230
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:47,112
I feel so bad for Tess and Mario.

231
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,201
I told you.

232
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:55,454
We should've doubled,
even tripled our shifts.

233
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,499
We didn't guard the place well enough.

234
00:15:58,582 --> 00:15:59,792
And now this happened.

235
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:03,462
We already doubled the watch.

236
00:16:05,172 --> 00:16:07,299
Maybe we just fell short.

237
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:09,885
What is it, B1? A picture?

238
00:16:11,428 --> 00:16:13,222
Hey! What are you doing?

239
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:16,225
Why are you taking pictures here?

240
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:17,601
Nothing.

241
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:18,769
Wait.

242
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,855
Aren't you the ones
who keep passing by here?

243
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:22,940
No.

244
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:24,233
Give them a hundred.

245
00:16:26,568 --> 00:16:28,320
- You should've shown them a hundred.
- A hundred?

246
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,155
- John! Take their picture!
- Give it to me.

247
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:31,657
You should've just said so.

248
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,367
- He's really good at taking pictures.
- Of course.

249
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,661
- There! There! There!
- There! There!

250
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:40,874
Isn't he the one
who keeps passing by here?

251
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:43,544
Ask him.

252
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:47,923
Hey,

253
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,758
are you the one who keeps passing by here?

254
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,010
No, that's not me.

255
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,386
Maybe it was B1.

256
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:54,096
Why me? It wasn't me.

257
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:58,475
He said he's not the one
who keeps passing by here.

258
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:00,102
- He's not?
- No.

259
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:02,563
I think it's him.

260
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,443
We can't bring back everything we lost.

261
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:13,365
But there are still things
we should be thankful for.

262
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:18,203
<i>Lord.</i>

263
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,039
<i>Thank you.</i>

264
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:24,168
<i>Despite everything, we're still alive.</i>

265
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:28,964
<i>Thank You so much for protecting us.</i>

266
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:34,803
<i>Thank You also</i>
<i>for letting me see my son again.</i>

267
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:38,223
<i>I won't ask for anything more.</i>

268
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:41,393
<i>If all of this is only borrowed,</i>

269
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:44,188
<i>thank You for the extra time.</i>

270
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,440
We're still here.

271
00:17:48,817 --> 00:17:50,861
Mario, we need to pray.

272
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:53,405
- Wait.
- Thank you, Captain Pepe.

273
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,824
Betchay! Wait, what about Betchay?

274
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:56,992
She'll follow later.

275
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:58,452
- Let's go. Come on.
- Come on.

276
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:03,290
Lord,

277
00:18:05,334 --> 00:18:07,961
please keep them all safe.

278
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:11,590
Especially Angelito.

279
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:16,053
Please watch over him
because he's not with us right now.

280
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:21,350
Please guide us all.

281
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,742
<i>I don't know what the next trial will be.</i>

282
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:43,288
<i>I don't even know if I made</i>
<i>the right decisions.</i>

283
00:18:44,289 --> 00:18:47,292
<i>But if I may ask,</i>

284
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:50,754
<i>please give us more strength</i>

285
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,882
<i>to face all of this.</i>

286
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,300
<i>And if possible,</i>

287
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:58,428
<i>give us a little more time,</i>

288
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:03,392
<i>a chance,</i>
<i>to be together and love one another.</i>

289
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:17,990
Are you done?

290
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:28,542
Let's go, Mikoy.

291
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,172
Tess, Mario, let's go.

292
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:07,414
Ouch.

293
00:20:10,834 --> 00:20:12,419
I wonder how Betchay is doing.

294
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,421
Yes.

295
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:16,590
Don't worry.

296
00:20:16,673 --> 00:20:18,759
Mario, Tess,

297
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:21,303
Betchay is sharp. She's like a cat.

298
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,387
She can handle this.

299
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:23,680
You have a point.

300
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:27,184
I'm going to miss that child of mine.

301
00:20:28,685 --> 00:20:29,811
Don't worry, my love.

302
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:33,941
You'll have more adopted children.

303
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,945
Mother Tess.

304
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:41,365
Come on now.

305
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:42,783
They have huge appetites.

306
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,870
By the way, this way.

307
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:50,165
Let's go. All right.

308
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:51,458
Go over there.

309
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:05,555
Wow, your place is so high up.
It's like Mount Everest!

310
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:08,767
You should've worn hiking shoes.

311
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:17,276
Goodness, come on. I'm starving.

312
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:20,153
Don't worry, my love.

313
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:21,613
I'm sure there's food there.

314
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:22,531
Okay.

315
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:25,993
Mikoy.

316
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,287
Where's Chiara? Why isn't she back yet?

317
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:33,101
Your mother never wanted to stay here.

318
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:36,938
But what can we do?

319
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:39,608
She's La Morte Bianca.

320
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:50,202
Even if it's La Morte Bianca.

321
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:52,621
Even if it's the Concordat.

322
00:22:55,957 --> 00:22:57,375
We can do something.

323
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:00,253
How?

324
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:36,331
I'm sure the police only wants to kill me.

325
00:23:41,294 --> 00:23:43,505
But first, I have to find the bomb.

326
00:23:43,588 --> 00:23:45,715
I have to beat Isabella to it.

327
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,393
What if Chiara needs help?

328
00:23:56,977 --> 00:23:59,020
Could we extract her?

329
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:01,356
That we are not sure of, right?

330
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:02,482
Why not?

331
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:05,610
If you and Chiara were together in Cebu,
it would've been easier.

332
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:07,821
<i>But if she's in</i>
<i>La Morte Bianca's territory,</i>

333
00:24:07,904 --> 00:24:09,197
it would put our team at risk.

334
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:13,577
There's a high chance
Chiara went back to the Moravianos.

335
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,328
What if they come after us here?

336
00:24:17,455 --> 00:24:18,415
What's that?!
